		<div id="post_message_1299758">
                  
                  Let me just be clear, I have not stopped playing because of the vast improvements to perfomance or the bug fixes.<br />
<br />
What has pushed me (and pushed me, and pushed me, time and time again) are the compleate overhauls to the games core features and systems in an atempt to gain apeal to more players.<br />
If they just focused on fixing the bugs, improving perfomance and adding content instead of re-vamping existing content over and over then they could re-launch the game and get a stable player base.<br />
<br />
As it is they have &quot;polished&quot; core systems so much that they bear no resemblance to the game I was promised and fell in love with. Its not any one thing, or even this GU as a whole, but this GU, after so many before just fails to deliver.<br />
<br />
From my perspective if there still tweaking the roles of crafted vs group vs raid gear like this, with a sledge hammer, after this amount of time, then there the stuff that trully matters to me, like breathing some life into a pretty but lifeless world, will not be addressed for years to come.<br />
<br />
No ill feelings to the dev team, or any players, rather best of luck. <br />
I've been patient and waited a year for SOE to back up its commitment to this game, but I'm just not seeing it forthcomming. If they were serious about finishing the game they would have invested in it rather than seek imediate return on investment by culling the staff back to the skelleton crew that currently maintains it.<br />
<br />
Cheers<br />
Code
                  
		</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
